    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00" n="440"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d440">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.5/3–950: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Embassy in the United Kingdom</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d440fn1">Repeated to Paris as 1028.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">secret   <gloss target="#t_niact1">niact</gloss>
                        </hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1950-03-09T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 9, 1950—7 p. m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1075. Pls deliver fol message from me to Bevin and Schuman if he is still in
                    London (latter through Fr Emb).</p>
                <quote rend="blockquote">
                    <p>“I believe that it wld be useful for us to meet again in the near future for
                        another discussion of common problems. I also think it wld be useful to hold
                        a mtg of the <gloss target="#t_NAT1">NAT</gloss> Council for a substantive
                        discussion by the 12 <gloss target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s on how our
                        common Pact objectives might be more vigorously pursued. This might mean a
                        mtg of several days. If convenient to you and the other <gloss
                            target="#t_FonMin1">FonMin</gloss>s I cld come to Europe for a week or
                        ten days beginning May 8. We are currently considering what topics cld most
                        profitably be discussed bilaterally, trilaterally and in the Council and wld
                        welcome your suggestions. I am sending a similar message to (Schuman-Bevin).
                        If you both think well of this suggestion I will take it up at once with the
                        other members.”</p>
                </quote>
                <p>Paris, please deliver above message if undelivered London.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
